President Biden visited a neighborhood in Queens, New York that was devastated by recent flooding caused by Hurricane Ida. He expressed his gratitude to the residents for their resilience and thanked local leaders, including Congresswoman Alexandria Ocasio-Cortez, for their efforts in helping the community. The President emphasized the urgent need to address climate change and its impact on extreme weather events. He pledged federal assistance and called for bold action to tackle climate change and build more resilient infrastructure. President Biden also highlighted his proposed infrastructure and climate change plans, which aim to create good-paying jobs and protect communities from future disasters. He urged unity and cooperation in addressing the climate crisis and emphasized the importance of helping one another in times of need.